summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 10002, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Jackson Street in the City of Seattle, from a point one hundred (100) feet east of Twelfth Avenue South to a point one hundred and fifteen (115) feet west of the east margin of Fourteenth Avenue South, by constructing therein a sewer of proper dimensions, in accordance with Resolution of the City Council of the City of Seattle, No. 728, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Immediate Payment," under the provisions of Ordinance No. 5693 of said city, approved December 6, 1899."
